**Constructed from a mix of antique and recycled parts, it stands at a proud five feet tall. The first three feet is a standard wooden post that supports the Free Little Library box, which is the remaining two feet in height. The Free Little Library box is made of a vintage wooden window pane with an antique, pull style, cabinet handle on the right side. The wooden frame of the window has been painted for a classic, vintage look. The window is mounted onto a wood frame recycled from various scraps of wood, making the structure sturdy and reliable. On top of the structure is a weathered, wooden roof to protect the books from the elements. Inside, shelves crafted from recycled lumber hold a variety of books.
